Hanalei Plans to Invest $49 Million in Romania, Mediafax Says

-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 
2011-07-18T06:34:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/hanalei-plans-to-invest-49-million-in-romania-mediafax-says.html
Hanalei Finance, a French private
equity company, plans to invest as much as 35 million euros ($49
million) in renewable energy in  Romania ,  Mediafax  reported
yesterday, citing Olivier Schorochoff, a manager at Hanalei’s
Windtechnics unit.  The company plans to start building next year a wind farm,
with a total capacity of 30 megawatts, in the southern Romanian
region of Dobrogea and a hydro power plant, at an unspecified
location in the country’s mountain region, according to the
Bucharest-based news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez in Prague at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  